Ramaphosa met with Mrwetyana's family in the Eastern Cape on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has described the death of University of Cape Town student Uyinene Mrwetyana as a watershed moment. Ramaphosa met with Mrwetyana's family in the Eastern Cape on Friday. Earlier this week, a Post Office employee confessed to raping and murdering Mrwetyana. Addressing the family, Ramaphosa said: “The death of your daughter and a number of other women who have been killed quite brutally across our nation, especially here in the Eastern Cape, is something that has gotten us to look at gender-based violence in a way that we must say we’ve reached a watershed moment.”' WATCH: #Uyinene Mrwetyana: 10 arrested during march against femicide in CT 